userStories.notes:
File: docs/content/docs/guides/plugin-development.mdx, lines 155-191.

The getItems tool code example shows a fetch() call formatted for ~80 chars:
```
handle: async params => {
    const response = await fetch('/api/items?' + new URLSearchParams({
      limit: String(params.limit ?? 20),
      ...(params.status && { status: params.status }),
    }), { credentials: 'include' });
```

The scaffolded project uses prettier with printWidth: 120 (configured in .prettierrc by the scaffold). When a developer copies this code verbatim into a scaffolded plugin, `npm run format:check` fails with 4 prettier errors.

The fix is to reformat the fetch() call to match what prettier with printWidth: 120 would produce:
```
    const response = await fetch(
      '/api/items?' +
        new URLSearchParams({
          limit: String(params.limit ?? 20),
          ...(params.status && { status: params.status }),
        }),
      { credentials: 'include' },
    );
```

This is the only code block in the documentation that has this issue. The first-plugin.mdx and resources-prompts.mdx examples all pass the scaffolded project's checks when copied verbatim (verified through testing).

IMPORTANT: Only change the formatting of the fetch() call in the getItems code block. Do not change any other code blocks or text in the file.
